As illustrated in FIG. 15, a signal processing device 900 configuring the abnormality determination device 100 includes the following configurations as an example:
a central processing unit (CPU) 901;
a read only memory (ROM) 902;
a random access memory (RAM) 903;
a program 904 loaded to the RAM 903;
a storage device 905 that stores the program 904;
a drive device 907 that performs read and write to a storage medium 906;
a communication interface 908 connected to a communication network 909;
an input/output interface 910 that inputs/outputs data; and
a bus 911 connecting the configuration elements.
